The reaction is terminated and the level of product generated is measured using the ADP Glo Assay Kit (Promega, Madison Wis.).

ADP Glo Assay: The ATPase assay is performed according the following protocol: Purified enzyme (20 nM p97), substrate (20 uM ATP) and a dose titration of compounds are mixed in buffer (50 mM TRIS pH 7.5, 20 mM MgCl2, 0.02% TX-100, 1 mM DTT, 0.2% (v/v) glycerol) and incubated at 37 C. for 15 minutes. The reaction is terminated and the level of product generated is measured using the ADP Glo Assay Kit (Promega, Madison Wis.).
